<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="secto3d">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>secto3d</refname>
    <refpurpose> 3D surfaces conversion</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>[m[,x]]=secto3d(seclist,npas)
[m]=secto3d(seclist ,x)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>seclist</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a list whose elements are (2,.) matrices</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>npas</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>an integer</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>m</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a matrix</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>x</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a vector</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
    Considering a surface given through a list <literal>seclist</literal> of sections in the 
    <literal>(x,z)</literal> plane  <literal>[m [,x]]=secto3d(seclist [,npas])</literal> returns a matrix <literal>m</literal>
    which contains a regular discretization of the surface.
  </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>The i-th row of the matrix m corresponds to the i-th section</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>The j-th column of m corresponds to the x(j)</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>
    Each section <literal>seclist(i)</literal> is described by a (2,.) matrix which gives respectively the x 
    and z coordinates of points.</para>
    <para><literal>[m]=secto3d(seclist ,x)</literal>in that case the x-vector gives the discretization 
    of the x-axis for all the sections</para>
  </refsection>
